## KEY MATHLIB DISCOVERIES

```lean
-- Covering space infrastructure (complete!)
import Mathlib.Topology.Homotopy.Lifting

-- Key lemmas:
IsCoveringMap.monodromy           -- fiber → fiber action
IsCoveringMap.monodromy_refl      -- monodromy of refl = id
IsCoveringMap.monodromy_trans_apply -- monodromy of trans = composition
IsCoveringMap.monodromy_bijective -- monodromy is bijective
IsCoveringMap.liftPath            -- path lifting
IsCoveringMap.eq_liftPath_iff'    -- uniqueness of lift

-- Circle specific:
Circle.isCoveringMap_exp          -- exp : ℝ → Circle is covering!
Circle.exp_eq_one                 -- exp r = 1 ↔ ∃ n : ℤ, r = n * 2π

-- Contractibility:
import Mathlib.Analysis.Convex.Contractible
RealTopologicalVectorSpace.contractibleSpace  -- ℝ is contractible

-- Simply connected:
import Mathlib.AlgebraicTopology.FundamentalGroupoid.SimplyConnected
SimplyConnectedSpace.ofContractible           -- contractible → simply connected
SimplyConnectedSpace.paths_homotopic          -- any two paths are homotopic
```

